# Microservices Architecture Guide

This guide explains how to use <%= baseName %> as a microservice in a JHipster microservices architecture.

## Overview

<%= baseName %> is configured as a **microservice** application. In this architecture:

- The microservice provides REST API endpoints only (no UI)
- A separate **gateway** application handles routing and UI serving
- Service discovery and configuration management are handled externally
- Each microservice can be independently deployed and scaled

